She would bring the life of Jesus Christ, the Savior of the world into the world.

54:46.919 --> 54:55.109
She would be an instrument to bring image bearers of God into the world and to disciple them so that they too will go wherever the lamb goes.

54:56.891 --> 55:04.580
And she will be a part in the hands of God of reversing the curse that she gave herself to.

55:04.840 --> 55:06.642
Listen to 1 Peter 3.7.

55:08.226 --> 55:16.235
Likewise, husbands, live with your wives in an understanding way showing honor to the woman as the weaker vessel.

55:17.636 --> 55:23.122
Since they are heirs with you of the grace of life so that your prayers may not be hindered.

55:24.123 --> 55:31.952
Husbands, if you don't live with your wife in an understanding way, God will close his ears to your prayers.

55:34.534 --> 55:37.938
And the reason is, is because you have been entrusted as a head

55:38.594 --> 55:42.039
over her life, all of us are created for headship.

55:43.120 --> 55:44.863
And Scripture lays out the order.

55:45.423 --> 55:55.237
A woman is to come under the headship of her father and then her husband because she has been created with a good and glorious role, but she is the weaker vessel.

55:56.879 --> 55:59.803
Now, obviously, we understand this to mean physically.

56:01.125 --> 56:07.794
What are we doing in this country by allowing women to go to the front lines of combat?

56:09.506 --> 56:14.654
My daughter will not be going to the front lines of combat over my dead body.

56:16.376 --> 56:20.102
What are we doing in this country putting women in men's sports?

56:21.204 --> 56:25.831
What kind of delusion are we living in that we're even having to talk about this?

56:26.352 --> 56:33.202
Of course, ordinarily women are weaker and smaller

56:33.442 --> 56:39.249
then men and every exception that a person can come up with only proves the rule.

56:41.212 --> 56:45.697
But what is it for woman to be the weaker vessel?

56:50.023 --> 56:56.030
Again, probably not going to be the most popular preacher of the year, but hang with me.

56:57.973 --> 57:02.098
I believe that women are also the weaker vessel

57:03.234 --> 57:11.682
in the sense that God has given them a nature, a constitution to nurture life, to bring life into the world.

57:11.762 --> 57:25.095
And even when they can't bring life into the world, women by the grace of God naturally nurture life, older women in our church nurture younger women and they promote life.

57:26.016 --> 57:31.922
Everything she touches comes to life and is exalted in glory and in beauty.

57:33.122 --> 57:41.933
And just like every other good virtue that God puts within us, Satan loves to manipulate that nurturing spirit.

57:43.395 --> 57:52.766
So what can so easily happen is that they who are made to nurture life, they who are made to build consensus by bringing families together.

57:52.806 --> 58:02.258
Their gifts can be exploited with deceptions and easily, ordinarily, a woman's emotions can be played on.

58:03.202 --> 58:06.246
because naturally she cares, naturally she coddles.

58:08.009 --> 58:16.561
And so just as easily a woman can be led astray by her emotions rather than subduing her emotions so that they're guided by truth.

58:18.143 --> 58:28.818
And so there's a deception that can very easily come, which is why God created them to be under the headship of a husband who loved them

58:28.930 --> 58:35.477
who lead them, who benevolently rule their homes for the good of all who are under their care.

58:37.199 --> 58:40.442
Women are biblically forbidden from ruling in the home.

58:41.463 --> 58:44.327
Women are biblically forbidden from ruling churches.

58:44.707 --> 58:50.833
Women are biblically forbidden from ruling communities, nations, and serving as civil magistrates.

58:52.475 --> 58:55.058
Because God did not create them for that.

58:55.970 --> 59:05.182
Isaiah 3 12 says that it is a cursed to be ruled by women because God did not create them for that role.

59:05.322 --> 59:07.324
It is a burden they were not made to bear.

59:09.127 --> 59:24.626
And the exception of Deborah who ruled Israel only proves the rule all the more that in exceptional cases of cowardly men, women oftentimes have to step forward when there are none around them willing to do it.

59:26.018 --> 59:33.467
Because she is an instrument of life and not of death, she is not to be leading into combat.

59:34.769 --> 59:35.690
And Deborah knew that.

59:36.731 --> 59:52.370
What women are to do is to participate in this glorious role of nurturing life, building families, building churches, teaching younger women and children under the headship of Christ.

59:53.058 --> 59:56.622
Listen to 1 Corinthians 11, the head of every man is Christ.

59:56.642 --> 59:59.585
The head of a wife is her husband and the head of Christ is God.

59:59.606 --> 01:00:14.282
1 Corinthians 14, 34, the woman should keep silent in the churches, for they are not permitted to speak, but should be in submission, as the law also says, if there is anything they desire to learn, let them ask their husbands at home.

01:00:15.824 --> 01:00:21.010
I believe they're talking about the gathering of the church on the Lord's Day, Sunday morning.

01:00:21.698 --> 01:00:30.844
So what this means is that a woman has a glorious role before God to bring forth this life in a way that no man ever could dream of doing.

01:00:30.884 --> 01:00:34.514
And yet her head

01:00:34.754 --> 01:00:42.222
is her husband or if she has no husband, her father or her family who step in to provide that protection for her.

01:00:42.482 --> 01:00:47.107
Her church who step in to provide that protection for her and listen to me men.

01:00:47.548 --> 01:00:53.053
It says that if they have questions first and foremost, let them ask their husbands at home.

01:00:53.414 --> 01:00:54.335
Do you know what that means?

01:00:55.616 --> 01:00:57.198
You have to know the answer.

01:00:57.258 --> 01:01:01.202
You better know it, buddy, because she's coming to you.

01:01:02.178 --> 01:01:04.841
You're her pastor before anybody else's.

01:01:06.143 --> 01:01:07.124
Now, please come to me.

01:01:07.184 --> 01:01:07.965
I'm your pastor.

01:01:07.985 --> 01:01:09.427
I want to talk to you.

01:01:09.487 --> 01:01:10.569
I want to work through this.

01:01:14.033 --> 01:01:20.862
But the last question that I want to ask and answer, and I don't know, maybe by Monday, I'll finish this sermon, but I can't stop now.

01:01:21.503 --> 01:01:22.404
Where is Adam?

01:01:23.866 --> 01:01:24.427
Where is Adam?

01:01:26.049 --> 01:01:26.389
I don't know.

01:01:26.449 --> 01:01:27.190
Maybe he's fishing.

01:01:28.031 --> 01:01:29.253
Could be in a hunting stand.

01:01:29.273 --> 01:01:30.194
Who knows?

01:01:30.850 --> 01:01:33.014
Maybe he's working legitimately.

01:01:33.054 --> 01:01:38.903
What we know about man is that man is supposed to be standing guard.

01:01:38.944 --> 01:01:50.283
And for whatever reason, whether physically he's present the whole time, which it seems that he is, or whether he's not, he is not standing guard.

01:01:51.665 --> 01:01:54.770
And that serpent knows to bypass the head

01:01:56.546 --> 01:02:11.970
and to jump the back of the fence rather than going through the gatekeeper, and he deceives the woman who is held fully responsible, and yet the man is an innocent bystander who is abandoned his post and letting all of it happen.

01:02:12.871 --> 01:02:13.752
So where is he at?

01:02:15.735 --> 01:02:16.476
Where is he at?

01:02:17.638 --> 01:02:25.330
Just as you see the wicked Ahab right behind him, you see Jezebel and the two are

01:02:26.210 --> 01:02:27.312
two peas in a pod.

01:02:28.533 --> 01:02:34.501
So turn back with man, let's bring conclusion to this matter in 2 Corinthians, in chapter 11, verse three.

01:02:36.624 --> 01:02:46.698
All of that is assumed when Paul says the same exact thing is happening in the church.

01:02:48.040 --> 01:02:55.250
Rather than coming through the gatekeeper, Satan is going after picking him off one at a time

01:02:56.898 --> 01:03:05.548
The church as Christ broad bypassing the Apostle Paul and she's being deceived by these cunning hucksters.

01:03:06.930 --> 01:03:08.272
And Paul said that it would happen.

01:03:09.253 --> 01:03:14.219
Wolves will spring up from among you and they will pick away the flock.

01:03:14.239 --> 01:03:22.629
It is a dangerous thing, ladies and gentlemen, Proverbs says when a man isolates himself because he becomes easy prey for the enemy.

01:03:24.251 --> 01:03:26.674
Second Corinthians 11-3, the word for thought,

01:03:26.818 --> 01:03:29.107
Five of the six uses are in 2 Corinthians.

01:03:29.127 --> 01:03:32.381
Your thoughts, your minds will be led astray.

01:03:32.602 --> 01:03:35.634
It refers to corruption, to moral ruin.

01:03:36.450 --> 01:03:39.193
We've already said to take every thought captive.

01:03:39.233 --> 01:03:45.099
Here's what happens when we don't do that from a sincere and pure devotion to Christ.

01:03:45.439 --> 01:03:48.923
It could read a simplicity that is in Christ.

01:03:49.223 --> 01:03:56.891
Ladies and gentlemen, I submit to you again, as I did last week and the week before Christianity is always won or lost in the mind.

01:03:59.854 --> 01:04:04.018
What do we allow to occupy our minds?

01:04:04.706 --> 01:04:10.354
What do we nurse and what do we rehearse in our heads day after day after day?

01:04:11.676 --> 01:04:22.352
Because what we allow to occupy, our minds becomes a fortress in our hearts and it controls our lives every single time.

01:04:22.793 --> 01:04:25.637
Guard the mind with all of your life.

01:04:27.320 --> 01:04:31.506
Don't empty the mind, fill the mind with the truth of God.

01:04:34.594 --> 01:04:37.617
Colossians 2 says that truth is laid out.

01:04:37.637 --> 01:04:45.386
So no one would delude you, take you captive because the implications are great.

01:04:45.486 --> 01:04:55.076
Any soldier who commits treason, any sailor who commits mutiny, any servant who betrays allegiance and disloyalty to his master, he knows the penalty is death.

01:04:56.417 --> 01:05:00.722
And death is what we rightly deserve because we have deserted God.

01:05:02.274 --> 01:05:07.613
And God paid the penalty of death so that we would never have to die again.

01:05:07.653 --> 01:05:09.018
Run to Him.

01:05:11.025 --> 01:05:14.898
So what is this sincere and pure devotion to Christ?

01:05:15.010 --> 01:05:17.714
Other translations just translate it simplicity.

01:05:18.115 --> 01:05:21.800
The word for sincere, it refers to a singleness of mind.

01:05:22.120 --> 01:05:24.063
It refers to a united purpose.

01:05:24.424 --> 01:05:28.009
It means that there are not divided loyalties and allegiances.

01:05:28.329 --> 01:05:30.613
It means that you're not straddling the fence.

01:05:30.913 --> 01:05:33.637
You're not conflicted in your loyalties.

01:05:33.657 --> 01:05:35.199
You're not duplicious.

01:05:35.600 --> 01:05:38.003
You're unswerving in your commitment.

01:05:38.023 --> 01:05:39.826
You have one aim.

01:05:40.066 --> 01:05:40.727
in life.

01:05:40.767 --> 01:05:44.733
2 Corinthians 5 says, and that is to please Jesus Christ.

01:05:45.034 --> 01:05:49.481
It's a single hearted devotion that will not be swayed.

01:05:49.701 --> 01:05:52.766
You will look no other way, but forward to the cross.

01:05:54.068 --> 01:06:00.338
Calvin said, is that which keeps us in the unadulterated and pure doctrine of the gospel?

01:06:02.050 --> 01:06:05.096
The word purity refers to moral blamelessness.

01:06:05.437 --> 01:06:15.478
These are the twin towers in our life that we are to guard with everything we have, our single-minded devotion and our puretiness, a purity of heart before the Lord.

01:06:16.840 --> 01:06:22.111
Paul says in 2 Corinthians 1, 12, he lived with simplicity and godly sincerity.

01:06:22.692 --> 01:06:23.474
He says in

01:06:23.778 --> 01:06:28.203
2 Corinthians 6, that he commends himself and it's by purity.

01:06:28.443 --> 01:06:37.033
He says in Ephesians 6, that servants are to obey their masters with a sincere heart.

01:06:37.053 --> 01:06:46.043
God give us this morning a sincere and pure devotion to Christ.

01:06:48.105 --> 01:06:52.210
I remember Jeremiah says the devotion of your youth.

01:06:52.962 --> 01:07:00.509
How you would have crawled over broken glass, three continents wide to be faithful to me.

01:07:01.250 --> 01:07:01.851
What happened?

01:07:03.392 --> 01:07:04.153
Come back today.

01:07:05.534 --> 01:07:18.787
Be cleansed in the fountain of his blood and be made pure and white as a virgin and as snow before God through the finished work of Jesus Christ and follow the Lamb wherever he goes.

01:07:20.509 --> 01:07:21.810
And be presented

01:07:22.466 --> 01:07:26.192
and all splendor and glory before him.

01:07:28.035 --> 01:07:29.117
Friends, don't flirt with it.

01:07:31.180 --> 01:07:44.862
For sake, the federal headship of Adam to which all of us find ourselves under men, women, boys and girls alike, we are under his headship and we are destined for death because Adam and sin is our master.

01:07:46.544 --> 01:07:47.506
Come back under.

01:07:48.418 --> 01:07:51.903
The headship of your Father in heaven through Jesus Christ.

01:07:52.183 --> 01:07:54.166
He is good and he is king.

01:07:55.688 --> 01:07:56.229
Let's pray.

01:07:58.992 --> 01:08:01.476
Father, would you help us?

01:08:03.058 --> 01:08:05.321
Me, the chief of which is in need of your help.

01:08:08.025 --> 01:08:12.872
Would you help us not to be led astray, but to have discernment?

01:08:14.313 --> 01:08:17.618
And would you renew within each one of us

01:08:18.114 --> 01:08:28.590
From the youngest to the oldest men and women of all stripes and backgrounds alike, or would you give us a sincere and pure devotion to Christ?

01:08:28.850 --> 01:08:33.998
Would you rekindle that within our souls this morning as our head?

01:08:34.018 --> 01:08:36.301
Lord, would you help us?

01:08:37.362 --> 01:08:42.710
Would you help me not to walk out from under your headship and be so easily deceived?

01:08:44.133 --> 01:08:47.858
But would you help me to love you and submit to you?

01:08:48.866 --> 01:08:49.634
And would you help us?

01:08:50.563 --> 01:08:51.815
In Jesus' name we pray.

01:08:52.926 --> 01:08:53.330
Amen.

